      "r-Clostridium Histolyticum Collagenase H sh-Oligopeptide-60 is a single chain recombinant fusion peptide, produced by fermentation in  E. coli.  The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from r-Clostridium Histolyticum Collagenase H and sh-Oligopeptide-60. The fusion peptide contains 936 amino acids and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
